---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import LessonShell from "../../components/LessonShell.astro";
import { LESSONS } from "../../data/curriculum";

const lesson = LESSONS.find((l) => l.id === "code-what")!;
---

<Layout title={`${lesson.title} · Learn AI`} description={lesson.blurb} currentId="code-what">
    <LessonShell lesson={lesson}>
      <p>
        A <strong>coding assistant</strong> lives where your code does — your terminal, your editor —
        and can read, edit, and run files with your approval. Examples:
      </p>

      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Tool</th><th>Surface</th><th>From</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Cursor</td><td>Editor (VS Code fork)</td><td>Anysphere</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Claude Code</td><td>Terminal CLI</td><td>Anthropic</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Codex CLI</td><td>Terminal CLI</td><td>OpenAI</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Windsurf</td><td>Editor (VS Code fork)</td><td>Codeium</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Antigravity</td><td>Desktop app + CLI</td><td>Google</td></tr>
          <tr><td>GitHub Copilot</td><td>Editor extension</td><td>GitHub</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Continue / Cline</td><td>VS Code extension</td><td>Open source</td></tr>
          <tr><td>aider</td><td>Terminal CLI</td><td>Open source</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="diff-grid">
        <div>
          <h3>Chat app</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Browser</li>
            <li>You copy/paste code</li>
            <li>No file access</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Coding assistant</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Terminal or editor</li>
            <li>Edits your files directly</li>
            <li>Runs your tests, your dev server, git</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>A typical session</h2>
      <pre>$ cd my-project
$ claude   # or: cursor . / codex / aider

› the app is crashing on startup, can you find why?

● reading package.json
● running npm start
● error: missing DATABASE_URL

I see — your app needs DATABASE_URL but .env doesn't have one.
Want me to add a placeholder + a clearer startup error?</pre>

      <div class="callout">
        <strong>Who it's for:</strong> people who write code. If you've never opened a terminal,
        start with a chat app — come back when you're ready to build something real.
      </div>
    </LessonShell>
</Layout>

<style>
  .diff-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1.2rem 0 1.6rem;
  }
  .diff-grid > div {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 0.9rem 1rem;
  }
  .diff-grid h3 { margin: 0 0 0.4rem; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .diff-grid ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.1rem; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  @media (max-width: 600px) { .diff-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
